inguished by the sign of a mole."],"variants":[{"name":"Van Mol","meanings":["Flemish and Dutch: habitational name for someone from Mol in Antwerp province, Belgium."]}]},{"name":"Blanche","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a nickname for a blonde, from <i>blanche</i>, feminine of Old French <i>blanc</i> ‘white’ (of Germanic origin). It came to be associated with the notion of whiteness as indicating purity, and was introduced into England as a given name by the Normans. A pale complexion combined with light hair was long an ideal of beauty in Europe (compare Modern English <i>fair</i>, which at first meant ‘beautiful’ and then, from the 16th century, ‘light in colouring’)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Blanche de DOL was born about 8 January 1152, in Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France. She had at least 1 daughter with Rollon de HARCOUET."},"et":{"ABT 08 JAN 1152–":"umbes 8. jaanuar 1152–Surnud","1138–1203":"1138–1203","1168–1234":"1168–1234","1152–Female":"1152–Surnud","1138":"1138","1203":"1203","1234":"1234","1168":"1168","ABT 08 JAN 1152":"umbes 8. jaanuar 1152","1152":"1152","about 1168":"umbes 1168","Dol-de-Bretagne, 35095, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, FRANCE":"Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"ABT 08 JAN 1152–":"noin 8. tammikuuta 1152–Kuollut","1138–1203":"1138–1203","1168–1234":"1168–1234","1152–Female":"1152–Kuollut","1138":"1138","1203":"1203","1234":"1234","1168":"1168","ABT 08 JAN 1152":"noin 8. tammikuuta 1152","1152":"1152","about 1168":"noin 1168","Dol-de-Bretagne, 35095, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, FRANCE":"Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Ranska","France":"Ranska"},"fr":{"ABT 08 JAN 1152–":"environ 8 janvier 1152–Décédée","1138–1203":"1138–1203","1168–1234":"1168–1234","1152–Female":"1152–Décédée","1138":"1138","1203":"1203","1234":"1234","1168":"1168","ABT 08 JAN 1152":"e